"use strict";
var inherits = require('../util').inherits;
var Injector = require('../Injector');
//var ResolutionError = require('../ResolutionError');
 
/**
 * @constructor
 * @extends Injector
 */
function AssignmentInjector(deps) {
  Injector.call(this, deps);
}
inherits(AssignmentInjector, Injector);
 
AssignmentInjector.injectorName = "assignment";
AssignmentInjector.createsInstance = false;
AssignmentInjector.allowsMultiples = true;
 
/** @lends AssignmentInjector# */
var CI = AssignmentInjector.prototype;
 
/**
 * Calls <code>new</code> on the component, passing in the list of dependencies as arguments.
 * @param instance {*} A previously resolved instance for the component.
 * @param component {Function} The component being resolved.
 * @param deps {{list: [], map: {}} A structure containing resolved dependencies to inject.
 * @return The instance that will be the result of the component resolution.
 */
CI.inject = function(instance, component, deps) {
  console.log("ASSIGNING", instance, component, deps);
 
  deps.list.forEach(function(dep) {
    console.log("FUCK", dep);
    Object.assign(instance, dep);
  });
 
  return instance;
};
 
module.exports = AssignmentInjector;
